      "content": "everything you say is just \"help is available\" and \"talk to someone.\" but no one can fix the fact that he's gone. it's like trying to patch a hole in a ship that's already at the bottom of the ocean. if the story is over, why am i being forced to sit through the credits alone in the dark? it just seems so cruel to keep existing when the person you existed for is just... gone. it feels like i'm just lingering where i don't belong anymore.",
